<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Himself" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Himself,</orth> 1) his own person; f. i. <cit><quote>that on h. such shame commits,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 9.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 9, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the king's son have I landed by h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.221" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 221</bibl></cit> (alone, unattended); cf. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 2, 30</bibl>. <cit><quote>take care for h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 257</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 2, 13</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the dog is h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>h. would lodge,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 143</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.146" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 146</bibl>. <cit><quote>to die by h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.2.111" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 2, 111</bibl></cit> (by his own hands). <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 3, 6</bibl>.<lb />2) in his own person; f. i. <cit><quote>got by the devil h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.319" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 319</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.107" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 107</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.211.107" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 211</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 1, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.119.71" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 119</bibl>.
<lb />3) refl.; f. i. <cit><quote>oared h. to the shore,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 119</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.394" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 1, 394</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.247" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 247</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.5.68" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 5, 68</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>